<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Berlese (1916) described 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" genus="Arthrhoplophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Prototritia">Prototritia</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1913" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1913" class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" genus="Arthroplophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Arthroplophora</taxonomicName>
(&quot; hoplophora &quot; is spelt here without initial h); he mentioned tridactyly of the legs as the single differential character. The type of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" genus="Prototritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Prototritia</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1913" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1913" class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" genus="Arthroplophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armadillo" subGenus="Prototritia">
Arthroplophora (Prototritia) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="armadülo" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">armadillo</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
that is described together with a second species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1913" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1913" class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" genus="Arthroplophora" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vulpes" subGenus="Prototritia" subGenus.outerRound="1">A. (P.) vulpes</taxonomicName>
. The subgenus is raised here to generic rank.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
Grandjean (1932, p. 29) pointed to the fact that the description of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" genus="Prototritia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Prototritia</taxonomicName>
, and in particular that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Berlese, 1913" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1913" class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" genus="Arthroplophora" genus.bestMatchDistance="54" genus.bestMatchVote="3" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armadillo" subGenus="Prototritia" subGenus.bestMatchDistance="54" subGenus.bestMatchVote="2" subGenus.innerRound="1" subGenus.outerRound="1">
A. (P.) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="armadülo" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">armadillo</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
reminds in some respects of 
<taxonomicName authority="Grandjean, 1932" authorityName="Grandjean" authorityYear="1932" class="Arachnida" family="Protoplophoridae" genus="Aedoplophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aedoplophora</taxonomicName>
, but that identity is precluded because of the number of &quot;coupures &quot; and the structure of the claw segment.
</paragraph>
